Details:
The Oregon Invasive Species Council is hosting its third statewide invasive species summit. The day-long event will bring together agency, industry, academic, and nonprofit leaders and legislators together to:
Listen from experts about the economic and environmental effects of invasive species that exist in other states/regions and are considered a high risk threat to Oregon;
Give Oregon legislators an opportunity to participate on a panel discussion to share their perspectives and views on funding mechanisms, policy, and public awareness of invasive species issues; 
Give Oregon natural resource agency directors an opportunity to participate on a panel discussion regarding the role of the Invasive Species Council and challenges implementing and prioritizing programs; and
Participate in interactive breakout sessions to develop priority actions to protect Oregon from the introduction and spread of invasive species.
Similar to previous summits, the outcome of this summit will be a set of actions the Oregon Invasive Species Council will take the lead on implementing.
